Evaluate each choice:<ul><li><strong>A: \(\cos Y\)</strong> — by co-function identity and direct ratio check, \(\sin X = \cos Y\). That matches choice A — <strong>A</strong> is correct.</li><li><strong>B: \(\cos X\)</strong> — \(\cos X =  rac{a}{c} 
eq  rac{b}{c} = \sin X\) unless \(a = b\) (isoceles). Not generally equal. Incorrect.</li><li><strong>C: \(	an Y\)</strong> — \(	an Y =  rac{a}{b} 
eq  rac{b}{c}\) in general. Incorrect.</li><li><strong>D: \(	an X\)</strong> — \(	an X =  rac{b}{a} 
eq  rac{b}{c}\) in general. Incorrect.</li></ul>
